                </p>

                <!-- United Kingdom Private Limited Company Section -->
                <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-2xl border border-blue-100 p-6 mb-8">
                    <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg mb-3">What Is a United Kingdom Private Limited Company?</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        A <strong>United Kingdom private limited company</strong> — written as "XYZ Ltd" or "XYZ Limited" — is the most common business structure in the UK. It is a legal entity entirely separate from its owners. This separation is what makes it so powerful:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-blue font-bold mt-0.5">→</span> <span>The company can own property, hold bank accounts, and sign contracts in its own name</span></li>
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-blue font-bold mt-0.5">→</span> <span>Shareholders' liability is <strong>limited to the value of their shares</strong> — personal assets are never at risk from business debts</span></li>
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-blue font-bold mt-0.5">→</span> <span>The company continues to exist even if directors or shareholders change — it has perpetual succession</span></li>
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-blue font-bold mt-0.5">→</span> <span>Corporation Tax rates of 19%–25% apply — far lower than personal income tax rates for higher earners</span></li>
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-blue font-bold mt-0.5">→</span> <span>Any nationality can form and direct a UK private limited company — no UK residency required</span></li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">
                        UK private limited companies are the preferred structure for founders from Pakistan, India, Bangladesh, the UAE, and across Southeast Asia who want access to global banking, Amazon FBA, Stripe, and international payment platforms.
                    </p>
                </div>

